<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-43-0724 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper describes the first part of the 'Test Program' performed atRiso National Laboratory, Denmark, under contract to the Commission ofthe European Communities (Joint Research Centre, Petten). The aim ofthe Test Program is to determine the suitability of existing standardsfor the control of radiographic image quality in neutron radiographyof nuclear reactor fuel. The other objective of the Program is to investigatewith what accuracy the dimensions can be measured from neutron radiographs.A description is given of the items under investigation, along with thetest programme, measuring instruments, dimensional measurements, andparts I and II of the test programme. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>